an essential component of a good old-time collection . gid tanner is a legendary old-time fiddler , so much so that old-time fans are frequently seen wearing t-shirts that say `` gid is my co-pilot '' . the old-time style here is , to discerning ears , quite different than the more common `` round peak '' style , made most famous by fiddler tommy jarrell , and quite obviously different than , say , ozark fiddling . none of the styles are any better or worse , just different , and serious old-time fans will enjoy picking apart the nuances of styles . more casual old-time fans will enjoy this record as well , though , for both the excellent repertoire and top-notch musicianship . if you think o brother where art thou is the real deal , i suggest picking this up and having a listen